BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:-dJLYOYPEHSEoRAKHh1E9
SUMMARY:SMB Marketing Webinar | 101: Community Partnerships & Micro-Influen
	cers
DTSTAMP:20260214T003546Z
DTSTART:20260224T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description    SMB Marketing Webinar | 101: Community Partnersh
	ips & Micro-Influencers Event Date: Monday\, February 24\, 2026 Event Time
	: 1:00 PM - 2:00 PM DESCRIPTION Join GSBA\, in partnership with Badolato C
	onsulting\, for a free webinar designed to help small and mid-sized busine
	sses prepare for and benefit from FIFA World Cup 2026. As Seattle prepares
	 to host matches and welcome international visitors\, local businesses hav
	e a unique opportunity to increase visibility\, build community connection
	s\, and drive long-term growth. This session will provide practical\, acti
	onable strategies that businesses can implement now to maximize the World 
	Cup&'s impact on their operations. Whether you run a restaurant\, retail s
	hop\, professional services firm\, or community-focused business\, this we
	binar will help you turn increased attention and foot traffic into lasting
	 customer relationships and revenue opportunities. What You'll Learn: Unde
	rstanding the FIFA 2026 Opportunity How increased international attention 
	and visitor traffic creates opportunities for local businesses The timelin
	e for World Cup preparations and when to launch your marketing efforts Bui
	lding Strategic Community Partnerships Creating win-win collaborations wit
	h neighboring businesses Developing co-marketing initiatives that amplify 
	reach without increasing costs Planning joint events and activations that 
	attract World Cup visitors Leveraging business districts and neighborhood 
	associations for collective impact Working with Micro-Influencers Identify
	ing local micro-influencers who align with your brand values Building auth
	entic partnerships with content creators in your community Structuring col
	laborations that deliver measurable results Using influencer content acros
	s multiple marketing channels Turning Short-Term Buzz into Long-Term Expos
	ure Building media relationships and securing PR coverage Creating shareab
	le moments that extend your reach beyond June 2026 Measuring success and R
	OI from your FIFA 2026 initiatives Who This Webinar Is For: This session i
	s ideal for GSBA members and Seattle-area small business owners who want t
	o: Increase visibility and foot traffic during the FIFA World Cup 2026 Bui
	ld partnerships with other local businesses and community organizations De
	velop cost-effective marketing strategies that maximize impact Create last
	ing customer relationships beyond the tournament Position their business a
	s part of Seattle&'s welcoming community No prior marketing experience nec
	essary. This webinar focuses on practical business development strategies 
	that any SMB can implement. Speakers   Michael Badolato Founder & Principa
	l\, Badolato Consulting Michael Badolato is the founder and principal of B
	adolato Consulting\, a strategic marketing and communications agency speci
	alizing in helping small and mid-sized businesses develop authentic commun
	ity partnerships. Michael is a GSBA member and active participant in Seatt
	le&'s small business community. Contact: michael@badolatoconsulting.com   
	 Alexander Goodman Marketing Strategist\, Badolato Consulting Alex Goodman
	 is a marketing strategist at Badolato Consulting with expertise in digita
	l marketing\, influencer partnerships\, and community engagement strategie
	s. Alex brings a data-driven approach to marketing strategy while emphasiz
	ing the importance of genuine relationships and community impact. Contact:
	 alex@badolatoconsulting.com    Molly Blaisdell PR Strategist & Consultant
	\, Badolato Consulting Molly Blaisdell has 25 years of experience in touri
	sm and lifestyle PR. She's won numerous awards and is involved with the So
	ciety of American Travel Writers.   About Badolato Consulting: Badolato Co
	nsulting is a strategic marketing and communications firm that helps small
	 and mid-sized businesses develop sustainable competitive advantages throu
	gh community partnerships\, strategic positioning\, and creative marketing
	 execution. Founded by Michael Badolato\, the firm specializes in helping 
	SMBs implement marketing strategies that deliver measurable results withou
	t requiring enterprise-level budgets.
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/smb-marketing-webinar-101
	-community-partnerships-micro-influencers/18089667/2026-02-24T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
